The paper analyzes the network structure of Twitter followership, which falls under the category of social networks. Therefore, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses network analysis techniques, which could fall under cs.SD (Software Development and Programming) or cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity and Privacy). Additionally, the paper discusses the manipulation of follower counts, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.CYBER. Finally, the paper proposes an alternative measure of popularity based on the number of friends, which could fall under cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences).
